genresAdvancedInfo.name: musica pernambucana
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Musica pernambucana is a Brazilian genre of music that originates from the state of Pernambuco. It is a lively and energetic style of music that is heavily influenced by African rhythms and melodies. Musica pernambucana is often associated with the traditional carnival celebrations in Pernambuco and is characterized by its use of percussion instruments, call-and-response vocals, and syncopated rhythms.
